      <body>
         <div type="letter">
        <opener><dateline><date when="1915-01-25">January 25, 1915</date></dateline>
             <salute>My dear <persName key="margaret_anderson">Miss Anderson</persName>:</salute></opener>
        <p>I see you are taking both poems, for which I am very pleased indeed.</p>
        <p>In the last line of <title level="a">“Ely Cathedral,”</title> will you please carry the <quote type="english">“praying for, by the bye?”</quote> up on the line with <quote type="english">“the red-flapped Bishop,”</quote> if you can get it in; if not, turn over <quote type="english">“by the bye.”</quote> The break in the line after <quote type="english">“joy”</quote> is correct, but the turnover was done by a stupid stenographer in <placeName key="london">London.</placeName></p>
        <closer>Yours sincerely,</closer>
       </div>
      </body>
